# TradeFlow environment variables (Firebase)
#
# Copy this file to ".env.local" and fill in the values from your Firebase
# project. Find them in the Firebase Console:
#   Project settings (gear icon) -> "Your apps" -> Web app -> SDK setup/config
#
# If you don't have a Web App yet: Project settings -> Your apps -> Add app ->
# Web (</>). Registering it gives you the apiKey and appId below.
#
# .env.local is git-ignored, so these never get committed.

# --- Firebase web app config (used by the browser + client code) ---
# These project-specific values are already known for "ammonssoftware":
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=ammonssoftware
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=25246724742
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=ammonssoftware.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=ammonssoftware.firebasestorage.app

# These come from registering a Web App (fill them in):
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# --- Seeding only (server-side, local development) ---
# The seed script (npm run seed) uses the Firebase Admin SDK, which needs
# Application Default Credentials. Easiest options:
#   1) Run: gcloud auth application-default login
#   2) OR download a service account key (Project settings -> Service accounts
#      -> Generate new private key) and set the path below.
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/absolute/path/to/serviceAccount.json
